OL,3,CCouncils and mayors urge government to
OL,4,Cgive them power to block betting shops
OL,6,FThe Commission also added that the
OL,7,Fgovernment plans to introduce new
OL,8,Fpowers, enabling local licensing
OL,9,Fauthorities to conduct cumulative
OL,10,Fimpact assessments.
OL,12,FOnce implemented, this could allow
OL,13,Fauthorities to consider factors such
OL,14,Fas socio-demographics when deciding
OL,15,Fwhether to grant or deny additional
OL,16,Fgambling premises licences.
OL,18,FThe only venues which can offer gaming
OL,19,Fmachines are casinos, Adult Gaming
OL,20,FCentres, pubs, betting shops and
OL,21,Farcades.
